HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 396
BY REPRESENTATIVE COATES
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Bella Cervantes for her advocacy for childhood cancer
awareness and positive impact on Louisiana
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Bella Cervantes, founder of Brave Bella Bead Co., for her courage,
3 entrepreneurial spirit, advocacy for childhood cancer awareness, and positive impact
4 on the state of Louisiana and beyond.
5 WHEREAS, Bella Cervantes of Hammond, Louisiana, is a remarkable young
6 entrepreneur, childhood cancer survivor, and inspirational role model whose story has
7 touched countless lives across the state and nation; and
8 WHEREAS, at the age of two, Bella was diagnosed with retinoblastoma, a rare form
9 of childhood eye cancer affecting only a small number of children each year, and she
10 courageously underwent life-saving treatment that resulted in the loss of her right eye; and
11 WHEREAS, through unwavering faith, determination, and perseverance, Bella
12 overcame tremendous obstacles; she is widely recognized as "Brave Bella" and inspires
13 others through her resilience and positive spirit; and
14 WHEREAS, Bella founded Brave Bella Bead Co. with the initial goal of saving
15 money for braces, but her business quickly grew into a mission-driven company dedicated
16 to spreading hope, encouragement, and awareness for childhood cancer; and
17 WHEREAS, Brave Bella Bead Co. creates handcrafted jewelry that is shipped across
18 the country and internationally and carries the company message: "Your Style. Your
19 Impact."; and
